. Different types of commentaries are described that target diverse audiences by using varied sets of commentary elements and compilatory techniques. Several commentaries are edited to illustrate the different commentary types.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aHebrew poetry, MedievalxHistory and criticismxGermany. 0aHebrew poetry, MedievalzGermanyxHistory and criticism. 0aJewish religious poetry, HebrewxHistory and criticismxGermany. 0aJewish religious poetry, HebrewzGermanyxHistory and criticism. 0aJudaismxHistoryxTo 1500xGermanyxGermany. 0aJudaismzGermanyxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aPiyutimxHistory and criticism. 4aHebräisch /Literatur, Literaturgeschichte. 4aJuden /Mittelalterliche Geschichte. 4aLiturgie. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / Theology.2bisacsh  aHebrew Poetry.  aJewish Liturgy.  aJews in Germany in the Middle Ages.  aMedieval Commentary.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023854908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2008z9783110212129oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2008z978311021213608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE/RELIGIONSWISS./JUDAISTIK  2008z9783110209280oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311019664140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311020409440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110204094423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110204094/original  a978-3-11-